rComments: "Weird, but likable. He read a poem on the first day of class and then walked out!"
If you get a chance, take the class. One of the best CMN profs I've ever had. Loved the book that he wrote specifically for the class. Makes theory interesting and looked forward to going to class.

Professor Conway is incredible. Half of your grade is based on weekly submissions and it's okay if you're wrong, as long as you submit it. Grades on attendance, but not participation. He is funny and you can tell he cares about students. Average amount of reading, but he makes the content easy to understand. Would highly recommend for CMN 3109!
10/10. Genuinely cares about his students. Thoughtful and engaging lectures. Actually makes the theory something worth discussing. WIsh I got the chance to take more classes with him

Kyle Conway was an incredible professor. He changed up his usual requirements for his CMN 3109 course this past semester (Winter 2020), making it more hands on and easier. He is super accessible and the most understanding prof I've ever had. Out of all of my profs he handled the COVID-19 pandemic the best, so online courses would be just as great.
Incredible professor. Clear & concise. Encourages learning & class discussion. Get ready to work.

Dr. Conway is inspiring. He's funny and he's paying attention the class at all times. If you have something to add, he'll never make you feel small. He is a kind and thoughtful professor and he'll take time for you after class if you ask for it. He is my favourite by a long shot. If you get a chance, take a class with him! You won't regret it.

Conway is amazing! He does a great job at applying theories so that they become practical. His lectures are worth attending, he breaks down an abstract textbook while keeping things entertaining. Exams are MC/matching and short answer. He doesn't try to trick his students and genuinely wants them to learn. One of the best profs I've had!
Amazing prof! Gave us cheat sheets to use during our tests. He makes the classes interesting, and you can really tell he has a passion for what he is teaching.

This prof really cares about his students. Well framed class and entertaining lectures, makes dense theory classes feel easier. Tough subjects are thoroughly explained, & students are welcome to ask questions. This class is heavy in complicated readings, but he'll explain everything. If you attend class and do the readings, you'll get a good mark.

Kyle is a great instructor; very knowledgeable. Quite a bit of reading, but mostly interesting stuff. Hard to know where you stand from a grade perspective until the very end. Kyle doesn't lecture much, but encourages student participation. When he does weigh in, though, he definitely knows his stuff.

Conway is amazing! He's young and funny and makes boring material actually kind of fun to learn about. He's very open to being challenged and hearing students' opinions. His exams are straightforward if you do all the readings and can argue a point of view. Must go to class or you won't understand readings!

In class unannounced participation questions (your own opinion about the question). The textbook is $$$, & a lot of reading, but break it down to the powerpoints, theories and their creator and you will do fine :) Very friendly and funny! Would definitely take his classes in the future. Two non cumulative midterms, final essay (no final exam).
Very good professor.
Favourite Prof I have had. Readings are tough but his lectures are extremely helpful and interesting. He is a very approachable person, funny, and passionate about his job. 100% recommend him!

I seriously love this guy so much. Best Professor in the Comms Department. Wish I had him for all my classes. Easy quizzes for participation mark, lectures are simple and easy to get. Gives lots of bonus questions.

Awesome professor. Really wants you to understand the material and cares about his students. Also reiterates the main concepts you need to know for midterms and gives a clear explanation of the grading criteria for all midterms/assignments. Would definitely take his class again.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Great professor

He is incredibly attractive to the extent where it is almost distracting. He is so relatable and incredibly welcoming and understanding. He gets the material is hard but does his best to make it easy. Just to reiterate incredibly attractive, like such a classically handsome man. I would put him in an old film with Marilyn Monroe he would fit.

Such a nice prof, his lectures aren't that clear but his exams are word for word the same as the slides.  Felt bad for him because everyone would get up and leave after the participation marks, but his exams and quizzes were veryy easy

SO glad i got him as a prof. the quizzes boost your mark a lot and all you have to do is go to class do do well, since the midterms a multiple choice. although i left halfway through the 3hr lecture almost every week and got 97% as a final mark. some lectures were a bit boring though. easy way to boost your gpa

This was a good class! He took very boring material and made it somewhat interesting. There was a lot of reading in this class and he actually removed some of the readings from the course as there were so many! We had weekly "quizzes" that we did at home and handed in each week. (basically attendance marks). DO the readingsquizzes and you're good

I have to say he is one of the best profs you could have. His lectures aren't that entertaining, BUT he gives you a lot of chances for marks with quizzes, and as long as you study his slides for the mid- terms and exam you will do great. I didn't study the 1st midterm & did poorly, but I studied the 2nd & got 94% & got 100% on his final exam.

He is by far one of my favourite profs. He makes boring material a lot better and has great lectures.  His in class quizes are easy if you read the readings and slide before class but can be a bit ambiguous sometimes. He really knows a lot about the topic. If you take notes and do the readings, you will do great. Highly recommended!!
Not only is his class super easy, he is a great lecturer. Would definitely recommend

Great teacher! He tried to keep the class interesting with videos, even though some material was boring. Let us leave early pretty much everyday and the quizzes were a good way to boost your grade! Exam questions were generally easy and straightforward. Not mandatory to attend but I would recommend it
Really good prof. Had an easy quiz every class for a grade booster. Exams are straightforward multiple choice.  Does try to keep it interesting.

Aside from the boring material, professor does an amazing job at trying to keep your attention. Assigns quizzes weekly, but they are very helpful to increase your grade if you do your readings before hand.

Awesome prof, has a lot of knowledge and information to offer. Lectures are really interesting and I found myself paying attention without even trying. His anecdotes about living in the States and his kids are funny and his teaching style overall is engaging. Would recommend :)
Super engaging and offers interesting perspectives of media. Would definitely recommend as a prof. I want to take more of his classes!
Great prof, took class as an elective and it was a great choice. Fun class, easy to get a good mark.
Awesome prof. Exams and quizzes are easy if you pay attention in class. He's really funny and engaging, I would 100% take another class with him. Gives a gret perspective on media.

Engaging, interesting lectures with a prof that makes it fun. Funny anecdotes, stories about his daughter and My Little Pony, and the videos he chooses to accompany his lectures make the class awesome. His teaching and the class actually convinced me to change majors! Great guy and great class!
great prof super funny

Overall, a fantastic prof. He seems to genuinely care about his students and has a great spin on Canadian media history by drawing on his knowledge of the States and his love of television. Hilarious, motivating, and straight forward. Quizzes are easy - do the readings and you'll be set.
Great guy!!!!!!!!!!
